main event: An unidentified aerial object was observed for a duration of 56 minutes in Webster Village, Maryland on April 3, 1953.
interesting points: The object was reported to be V-shaped and had no visible vapor or exhaust trails., No photographs were taken during the sighting., Visibility conditions were cloudy with a two-mile range., The observation was made by a civilian ground observer named Patrick Lynch., No electronic equipment was used to track the object.
witness description: Patrick Lynch, civilian ground observer volunteer
